Section V CTAN Edition

Welcome to the XML based and XSL generated version of The TeX Catalogue Online, Section V CTAN Edition. This is a listing of entries in the TeX Catalogue and may take a little time to load, but is hopefully worth it. Have a look at the Catalogue Preface for alternative ways of accessing the catalogue.

The TeX Catalogue Online is also available from any CTAN node or mirror, including the following. Pick one that is close to you. (The "search" link attempts to find a CTAN node that may be close to you, courtesy of Randy Kobes. Multiple clicks may find alternatives.)

Icons associated with many entries in the catalogue allow you to:

  • view the directory on CTAN
  • view documentation (possibly many)
  • view documentation in PDF format (requires the acroread plugin)
  • jump to the package's home page
  • download a gzip'd tar file from a nearby CTAN node (not supported by all nodes)
  • download a gzip'd tar file from ftp.dante.de

Other icons simply provide further information about the package:

  • part of the teTeX distribution
  • available on the TeX Live CD ROM

The license type, version (if known), and the date of the last change made to each particular Catalogue entry are also provided.

A system to support the writers of virtual fonts; this is written in Turbo Pascal, and sources are included.

vfinst No caption.
A set of scripts and Perl files which aim to make the installation of families of PostScript fonts and creation of necessary virtual fonts outline fonts `virtually' automatic. Uses fontinst.

viiptart No caption.
An article-like document class which is 7pt rather then 10pt.

vita No caption.
This class provides necessary macros to prepare your Curriculum Vitae or Resume.
license: unknown (1 Apr 1991)
vmargin No caption.
Provides a macro to set various margins as well as dimensions for header/footer and page dimensions. Most common paper sizes and two sided printing are supported. See also geometry typearea
license: dfsg (1996/06/12)
vncmr A Vietnamese extension of the cmr fonts.
Contains MetaFont source files, tfm files, and various LaTeX2e and plain TeX files for VISCII encoding.
license: gpl (1999/03/03)
vrb Verbatim macros via plain TeX.
See also alltt moreverb verbatim
license: unknown (1999/03/03)
vrsion No caption.
Defines a command which produces a version number in the dvi-file when LaTeX is run.
license: unknown (1998/07/8)
vruler No caption.
A package for adding a vertical numbering to the general text so that the text can be properly referenced. The vertical ruler can be scaled and moved freely. Supports LaTeX and plain TeX.
license: unknown (1996/10/24)
